Ingest_LDD.name: OSIRIS-REx Mission Dictionary
Ingest_LDD.comment: This is the OSIRIS-REx Mission Specific Data Dictionary.

DD_Attribute.name: action_mode
DD_Attribute.definition: Action sequence enable mode: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: active
DD_Attribute.definition: Camera number of active camera (1-Map, 2-Sam, 3-Poly). Note that the numeric values are different than those of the CAMERAID.

DD_Attribute.name: adc_clamp_enable
DD_Attribute.definition: Analog to digital converter clamp enable during imaging. Enable equals 1.

DD_Attribute.name: apid
DD_Attribute.definition: Application Identification Number

DD_Attribute.name: att_rate_x
DD_Attribute.definition: The x-axis component of the spacecraft angular rate in spacecraft body frame at the ATT_TIME

DD_Attribute.name: att_rate_y
DD_Attribute.definition: The y-axis component of the spacecraft angular rate in spacecraft body frame at the ATT_TIME

DD_Attribute.name: att_rate_z
DD_Attribute.definition: The z-axis component of the spacecraft angular rate in spacecraft body frame at the ATT_TIME

DD_Attribute.name: att_time
DD_Attribute.definition: The spacecraft clock time when attitude data was collected

DD_Attribute.name: bennana
DD_Attribute.definition: Azimuth of the North polar Axis of the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu), positive from the +NAXIS2 direction toward the +NAXIS1 direction; see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value; assumes undistorted optics; will be -999 if the calculation fails

DD_Attribute.name: bennu_dec
DD_Attribute.definition: Declination of the vector, expressed in the Earth Mean Equator of the J2000 Epoch, from the ORX spacecraft toward the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value

DD_Attribute.name: bennu_naxis1_offset
DD_Attribute.definition: Approximate offset from CRPIX1 pixel in +NAXIS1 direction of the location of the center of the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value; assumes undistorted optics

DD_Attribute.name: bennu_naxis2_offset
DD_Attribute.definition: Approximate offset from CRPIX2 pixel in +NAXIS2 direction of the location of the center of the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value; assumes undistorted optics

DD_Attribute.name: bennu_ra
DD_Attribute.definition: Right Ascension of the vector, expressed in the Earth Mean Equator of the J2000 Epoch, from the ORX spacecraft toward the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value

DD_Attribute.name: bennu_radec_quality
DD_Attribute.definition: (Quality: provenance) for the BENNURA, BENNUDEC, BENNUNX1, BENNUNX2 FITS keywords. This will be one of three values: (BEST: SPK), meaning the geometry was obtained from SPICE SP-Kernels; (POOR: osculating elements; +/-1E6km), meaning the geometry was obtained from osculating orbital elements of Bennu w.r.t the Sun, and will have uncertainties of order 1E6km; (NONE: FAILURE), meaning both the SPK and elements methods failed; the parentheses, (), are only delimiters here and not part of the quality:provenance values.

DD_Attribute.name: bennu_radec_target
DD_Attribute.definition: Target for the BENNURA, BENNUDEC, BENNUNX1 and BENNUNX2 FTIS keywords; typically BENNU; may be NONE if the calculation failed. Target is not required to be in the field of view.

DD_Attribute.name: board_rev_num
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD board revision number

DD_Attribute.name: bore_angle
DD_Attribute.definition: Angle between boresight and origin of Bennu in planetocentric Cartesian coordinates

DD_Attribute.name: bore_flag
DD_Attribute.definition: Boresight flag 0-Boresight does not intersect surface of asteroid; 1-Boresight intersects surface of asteroid

DD_Attribute.name: boresight_lat
DD_Attribute.definition: Boresight latitude of the imaging location

DD_Attribute.name: boresight_lon
DD_Attribute.definition: Boresight longitude of the imaging location

DD_Attribute.name: boresight_range
DD_Attribute.definition: Range from spacecraft to the closest boresight intersection to spacecraft. Must be positive number . If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be 0.0

DD_Attribute.name: boresight_x
DD_Attribute.definition: X coordinate of boresight intersection with surface in planetocentric Cartesian coordinates. Allowed range 0 to 1000.0. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be 0.0

DD_Attribute.name: boresight_y
DD_Attribute.definition: Y coordinate of boresight intersection with surface in planetocentric Cartesian coordinates. Allowed range 0 to 1000.0. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be 0.0

DD_Attribute.name: boresight_z
DD_Attribute.definition: Z coordinate of boresight intersection with surface in planetocentric Cartesian coordinates. Allowed range 0 to 1000.0. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be 0.0

DD_Attribute.name: bpp
DD_Attribute.definition: Records the pixel depth of the transmitted image. If the image was initially acquired as 12 bits, then it can be sent as 12 bits or 8 bits. If the image was initially acquired as 8 bits, then this value is ignored and the output is always 8 bits. The companding mode is only significant if companding is turned on. Keyword may be blank if the transmit-image-raw command was used to acquire image.

DD_Attribute.name: cal_lamp_sel
DD_Attribute.definition: Bitwise Camera of the active illumination lamp

DD_Attribute.name: calrad_used
DD_Attribute.definition: Indicates the calibration method used. 1 - nominal space looks, 2 - infrequent space looks, 3 - no space looks

DD_Attribute.name: camera_head_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: Camera head temperature in digital number (if available).

DD_Attribute.name: camera_id
DD_Attribute.definition: ID of camera in use. 0- Map, 1-Sam, 2-Poly. Note that the numeric values for ACTV_CAM are different, but the named camera will be identical.

DD_Attribute.name: ccd_csr_reserved
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD control status register reserve bit

DD_Attribute.name: ccd_rev_num
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD revision number

DD_Attribute.name: ccd_rst_l_pulse
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD control status reg left reset pulse indicator. 1 equals 25 ns RST_L pulse , 0 equals 12.5 ns (Control/Status) Note: if ADC_INCLK equals 10 MHz, RST_L is forced to 12.5 ns.

DD_Attribute.name: ccd_rst_r_pulse
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD control status reg right reset pulse indicator. 1 equals 25 ns RST_R pulse, 0 equals 12.5 ns (Control/Status) Note: if ADC_INCLK equals 10 MHz, RST_R is forced to 12.5 ns.

DD_Attribute.name: cd1_1
DD_Attribute.definition: Change in RA per pixel along first axis (sample) evaluated at reference pixel

DD_Attribute.name: cd1_2
DD_Attribute.definition: Change in RA per pixel along second axis (line) evaluated at reference pixel

DD_Attribute.name: cd2_1
DD_Attribute.definition: Change in DEC per pixel along first axis (sample) evaluated at reference pixel

DD_Attribute.name: cd2_2
DD_Attribute.definition: Change in DEC per pixel along second axis (line) evaluated at reference pixel

DD_Attribute.name: chan1_course_dac_reg_val
DD_Attribute.definition: Channel 1 coarse DAC register. 0 equals off, 1 equals on.

DD_Attribute.name: chan1_fine_dac_reg_val
DD_Attribute.definition: Channel 1 fine DAC register. 0 equals off, 1 equals on.

DD_Attribute.name: chan2_course_dac_reg_val
DD_Attribute.definition: Channel 2 coarse DAC register. 0 equals off, 1 equals on.

DD_Attribute.name: chan2_fine_dac_reg_val
DD_Attribute.definition: Channel 2 fine DAC register. 0 equals off, 1 equals on.

DD_Attribute.name: checksum_result
DD_Attribute.definition: The pass/fail state of the image check sum

DD_Attribute.name: ckqual
DD_Attribute.definition: Quality of C-Kernel (nominal equals RECONSTRUCT, contingency equals PREDICT)

DD_Attribute.name: control_file
DD_Attribute.definition: Data origin/provenance information

DD_Attribute.name: creator
DD_Attribute.definition: Creator of this product

DD_Attribute.name: cs1h_ccd
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD Storage clock pattern. CCD Storage clock patterns during a storage to horizontal register transfer. There are 8 bit periods per storage clock cycle. The CS1H_CCD determines the high to low ratio incremented each VFREQCSR count cycle.

DD_Attribute.name: cs2h_ccd
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD Storage clock pattern. CCD Storage clock patterns during a storage to horizontal register transfer. There are 8 bit periods per storage clock cycle. The CS2H_CCD determines the high to low ratio incremented each VFREQCSR count cycle.

DD_Attribute.name: cs3h_ccd
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD Storage clock patterns during a storage to horizontal register transfer. There are 8 bit periods per storage clock cycle. The CS3H_CCD determines the high to low ratio incremented each VFREQCSR count cycle.

DD_Attribute.name: cs4h_ccd
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD Storage clock patterns during a storage to horizontal register transfer. There are 8 bit periods per storage clock cycle. The CS4H_CCD determines the high to low ratio incremented each VFREQCSR count cycle.

DD_Attribute.name: ctype1
DD_Attribute.definition: Coordinate type for reference pixel, values are either RA---TAN equals gnomic or tangent plane or SIP - simple image polynomial.

DD_Attribute.name: ctype2
DD_Attribute.definition: Coordinate type for the reference pixel, values are either DEC--TAN equals gnomic or tangent plane or SIP - simple image polynomial.

DD_Attribute.name: cunit1
DD_Attribute.definition: Units for reference pixel 1 (CRPIX1)

DD_Attribute.name: cunit2
DD_Attribute.definition: Units for reference pixel 2 (CRPIX2)

DD_Attribute.name: cur_detector_minus_24
DD_Attribute.definition: -24 V current detector

DD_Attribute.name: cur_detector_minus_24_x
DD_Attribute.definition: -24 V current detector

DD_Attribute.name: cur_detector_plus_24
DD_Attribute.definition: +24 V current detector

DD_Attribute.name: cur_detector_plus_24_x
DD_Attribute.definition: +24 V current detector

DD_Attribute.name: cur_detector_plus_5
DD_Attribute.definition: +5 V current detector

DD_Attribute.name: cur_detector_plus_5_x
DD_Attribute.definition: +5 V current detector

DD_Attribute.name: cur_htr
DD_Attribute.definition: Heater Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_htr_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Heater Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_index
DD_Attribute.definition: Index Lamp Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_index_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Index Lamp Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_lamp
DD_Attribute.definition: Illumination Lamp Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_lamp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Illumination Lamp Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_motor
DD_Attribute.definition: Motor Current

DD_Attribute.name: cur_motor_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Motor Current

DD_Attribute.name: cx_pattern
DD_Attribute.definition: CCD vertical clock pattern. There are 8 bit periods per vertical clock cycle. CX_PATT determines the high to low ratio incremented each VFREQCSR count cycle.

DD_Attribute.name: data_source
DD_Attribute.definition: Origin of image data TEST or FLIGHT

DD_Attribute.name: date_of_observation
DD_Attribute.definition: Observation start time in UTC (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss)

DD_Attribute.name: declination
DD_Attribute.definition: Boresight Declination (DEC) in J2000 frame

DD_Attribute.name: delta_obs
DD_Attribute.definition: Delta between mid-observation time and spacecraft clock string (Mid-observation time) - (SCLK_STR timestamp), in seconds used to verify exposure time.

DD_Attribute.name: detector_mode
DD_Attribute.definition: Imaging command mode.

DD_Attribute.name: device_id
DD_Attribute.definition: Analog to digital converter device revision identifier

DD_Attribute.name: dispornt
DD_Attribute.definition: Image origin (0,0) is located in the bottom-left corner of the display. This is the standard FITS display orientation.

DD_Attribute.name: dpu_brd_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: Digital processing unit (DPU) board temperature.

DD_Attribute.name: dpu_brd_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: DPU Board Temperature

DD_Attribute.name: effective_exposure
DD_Attribute.definition: The effective exposure time after charge smear removal

DD_Attribute.name: egain
DD_Attribute.definition: Electronic gain in electrons per analog-to-digital units

DD_Attribute.name: emission_angle
DD_Attribute.definition: Emission angle. The angle between the vector normal to the surface at the location of the boresight intersection with the surface and the vector pointing to the Spacecraft. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then sub-spacecraft point shall be used. Allowed range is 0.0 to 90.0

DD_Attribute.name: emission_angle_sis
DD_Attribute.definition: Emission angle. The angle between the vector normal to the surface at the location of the boresight intersection with the surface and the vector pointing to the Spacecraft. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 90.0

DD_Attribute.name: encode_upper_pixel_bits
DD_Attribute.definition: Charge couple device control status register 1 equals encode upper pixel bits

DD_Attribute.name: equinox
DD_Attribute.definition: Epoch of mean equator and equinox (J2000)

DD_Attribute.name: expo_ms
DD_Attribute.definition: Exposure time in milliseconds

DD_Attribute.name: exposec
DD_Attribute.definition: Exposure time in seconds

DD_Attribute.name: exposure
DD_Attribute.definition: Exposure time in seconds

DD_Attribute.name: file_creation
DD_Attribute.definition: Date of creation of this file

DD_Attribute.name: filtname
DD_Attribute.definition: Filter name: SS - sun safe, X - 860 nm filter, W - 700 nm filter, V - 550 nm filter, B - 470 nm filter, PAN - panchromatic filter focused at greater than or equal to 125 m, SSCAL - sun safe blocking filter calibration prosition, PAN30 - panchromatic filter focuses at 30 m, PAN1 - panchromatic filter focused at 5 m, PAN4 - panchromatic filter focused at 5 m , PAN5 - panchromatic filter focused at 5 m

DD_Attribute.name: fov_fill_factor
DD_Attribute.definition: Fill Factor. If FOV Flag equals 2, describes the fraction of the FOV that intersects the asteroid surface. If FOV Flag equals 0, value shall be 0.0. If FOV Flag equals 1, value shall be 1.0. Allowed range is 0.0 to 1.0

DD_Attribute.name: fov_fill_flag
DD_Attribute.definition: Field of view flag 0-Entire FOV images empty space; 1-Entire FOV image s asteroid surface; 2-Portion of FOV images empty space

DD_Attribute.name: fpa_moly_a_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: FPA Moly (Molybdenum) A Temperature Monitor

DD_Attribute.name: fpga_rev_num
DD_Attribute.definition: FPGA revision number

DD_Attribute.name: gain
DD_Attribute.definition: The sensor analog gain value to use. Legal values are 8-31 and 40-63. Values from 8 to 31 specify gains in the range 1 to 3.875 in steps of 0.125; values from 40 to 63 specify gain in the range 2 to 7.75 in steps of 0.25. Gains in the range [2, 4) should be commanded using the first range

DD_Attribute.name: giant_ckqual
DD_Attribute.definition: Quality of pointing (nominal equals RECONSTRUCT or C-SMITHED(GIANT), contingency equals PREDICT)

DD_Attribute.name: ground
DD_Attribute.definition: Ground (Analog)

DD_Attribute.name: ground_receipt_time
DD_Attribute.definition: Ground Receive Time in UTC (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss)

DD_Attribute.name: ground_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Ground (Analog)

DD_Attribute.name: hcte_csr
DD_Attribute.definition: Horizontal over scan count

DD_Attribute.name: htr_brd_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: Heater board temperature (unbuffered)

DD_Attribute.name: htr_brd_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Heater_BRD_Temp (unbuffered)

DD_Attribute.name: htr_test_pt
DD_Attribute.definition: Ground (Analog)

DD_Attribute.name: htr_test_pt_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Ground (Analog)

DD_Attribute.name: image_id
DD_Attribute.definition: Identifier that is associated with an image

DD_Attribute.name: image_len
DD_Attribute.definition: Recorded image length

DD_Attribute.name: image_size_estimate
DD_Attribute.definition: initial size estimate for image in flash

DD_Attribute.name: image_type_code
DD_Attribute.definition: Type of image commanded. LIGHT (science observation), BIAS (calibration) , DARK (calibration), LAMP (calibration), OTHER

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_cam
DD_Attribute.definition: Specifies which camera to use. Legal values are 1 (for both DVR-4s) and 2 (for the DVR-4 with StowCam attached).

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_compress
DD_Attribute.definition: Take image hardware image compression mode. 0 means no compression; 0xff means lossless compression; 1-99 means JPEG compression quality N, 4:2:2 color subsampling if applicable; 101-199 means JPEG compression quality N, 4:4:4 color subsampling if applicable. Hardware compression is only available in 8-bit mode; if companding is turned off, this value must be 0.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_exp
DD_Attribute.definition: The commanded 16-bit exposure time for each image. For values from 0 to 5000, exposure time is in units of 0.1 msec, providing exposures of 0 to 0.5 seconds. From 5001 to 65535, exposure time is in units of 0.5msec with an offset of 0.5 seconds, so that the maximum exposure time is 0.5e-3*(65535-5000)+0.5 equals 30.7675 seconds.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_gain
DD_Attribute.definition: The sensor analog gain value. Legal values are 8-31 and 40-63. Values from 8 to 31 specify gains in the range 1 to 3.875 in steps of 0.125; values from 40 to 63 specify gain in the range 2 to 7.75 in steps of 0.25. Gains in the range (2, 4) are commanded using the first range

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_h
DD_Attribute.definition: The starting height of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_int
DD_Attribute.definition: The 16-bit time interval between images in seconds, from 0 (as fast as possible) to 65535 seconds.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_mode
DD_Attribute.definition: 0- 12-to-8 bit companding on/off; 1-3 companding mode (0 equals square root, 1-7 linear divide by exp2(N-1)); 4- dark pixels on/off; test pattern control (on equals 1/off equals 0); 6 enable additional sensor register settings (enable equals 1/disable equals 0); 7 reserved

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_num_imgs
DD_Attribute.definition: The number of images to acquire in this sequence. Legal values are 1 to 255.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_opcode
DD_Attribute.definition: TAGCAMS Command 8-bit Operations Code (Opcode)

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_seq
DD_Attribute.definition: The sequence identifier to assign to these images. Legal values are 1 to 255.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_subsample
DD_Attribute.definition: The subsampling to use when acquiring the image. Legal values for this field are 0 (no subsampling), 1 (bin 2x2), 4 (bin 4x4), and 16-23 (skip (N-14)*(N-14)).

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_sx
DD_Attribute.definition: The starting X of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_sy
DD_Attribute.definition: The starting Y of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

DD_Attribute.name: img_cmd_w
DD_Attribute.definition: The starting Z of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

DD_Attribute.name: imgs_to_capture
DD_Attribute.definition: Number of images to capture (Control/Status) Minimum/Default equals 1; Maximum equals 28

DD_Attribute.name: incidence_angle
DD_Attribute.definition: Incidence angle. The angle between the vector normal to the surface at the location of the boresight intersection with the surface and the vector pointing at the Sun. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then sub-spacecraft point shall be used. Allowed range is 0.0 to 90.0

DD_Attribute.name: incidence_angle_sis
DD_Attribute.definition: Incidence angle. The angle between the vector normal to the surface at the location of the boresight intersection with the surface and the vector pointing at the Sun. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 90.0

DD_Attribute.name: index_led_read
DD_Attribute.definition: Bitwise read of the active LED sensors

DD_Attribute.name: index_led_sel
DD_Attribute.definition: Camera number of the active motor index LED set

DD_Attribute.name: int_time
DD_Attribute.definition: Commanded exposure time in milliseconds

DD_Attribute.name: latitude
DD_Attribute.definition: Planetocentric latitude of boresight intersection with the surface. Allowed range +90.0 to -90.0. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be -9999

DD_Attribute.name: linearity_limit
DD_Attribute.definition: Linearity Limit.

DD_Attribute.name: longitude
DD_Attribute.definition: Planetocentric longitude of boresight intersection with the surface. Allowed range 0 to 360. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be -9999

DD_Attribute.name: lut
DD_Attribute.definition: Currently selected LUT number: 0 equals None. The description of this field will be updated as more LUTS are added.

DD_Attribute.name: lvps_brd_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: Low voltage power supply (LVPS) board temperature

DD_Attribute.name: lvps_brd_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: LVPS Board Temperature

DD_Attribute.name: main_config
DD_Attribute.definition: Main configuration

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_ccd_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam CCD heater, on/off state

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_ccd_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam CCD resistance temperature detector temperature

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_ccd_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam CCD resistance temperature detector (RTD) temperature

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_filt_house_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: State of the heater: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_filt_motor_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: State of the heater: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_fwh_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Filter Wheel Housing Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_fwh_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Filter Wheel Housing Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_fwm_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Filter Wheel Motor Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_fwm_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Filter Wheel Housing Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_len_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Lens Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_len_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Lens Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_lens_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: State of the heater: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_readout_elect_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: State of the heater: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_roe_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Read Out Electronics Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: mapcam_roe_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: MapCam Read Out Electronics Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: max_pixel_value
DD_Attribute.definition: Max image pixel value in dynamic range recorded by the instrument.

DD_Attribute.name: meta_ker
DD_Attribute.definition: Metakernel that holds all the spice kernels used for processing

DD_Attribute.name: mid_obs
DD_Attribute.definition: Spacecraft mid-exposure time, UTC [Cal d] (DATE_OBS - .5*EXPTIME).

DD_Attribute.name: mid_obs_et
DD_Attribute.definition: The ephemeris time of the mid-exposure time, mid_obs

DD_Attribute.name: mid_obs_sclk
DD_Attribute.definition: The SCLK string of the mid-exposure time, mid_obs

DD_Attribute.name: min_cnt
DD_Attribute.definition: Number of minutes since reset

DD_Attribute.name: min_pixel_value
DD_Attribute.definition: Max image pixel value in dynamic range recorded by the instrument.

DD_Attribute.name: mission_phase_identifier
DD_Attribute.definition: Abbreviation used to indicate the OSIRIS-REx mission phase. Accepted values are lau for Launch, obc for Outbound Cruise, app for Approach, psv for Preliminary Survey, ora for Orbit A, dsv for Detailed Survey, orb for Orbit B, rec for Recon, tar for TAG Rehearsal, tag for Touch-and-Go, and rtn for Return Cruise.

DD_Attribute.name: mission_phase_name
DD_Attribute.definition: Mission phase of the OSIRIS REx mission. Mission phase possibilities include cruise, approach, preliminary survey, orbital a, detailed survey, orbital b, reconnaissance, rehearsal, and TAG (Touch-and-go)

DD_Attribute.name: mission_subphase_name
DD_Attribute.definition: Mission subphases of the OSIRIS REx mission.

DD_Attribute.name: misspxla
DD_Attribute.definition: Number of pixels in the 1024x1024 active area that were zero filled as a result of data loss

DD_Attribute.name: misspxls
DD_Attribute.definition: Number of pixels in the entire 1112x1044 CCD that were zero filled as a result of data loss

DD_Attribute.name: mk_filename
DD_Attribute.definition: Filename of the meta-kernel created for processing this Level0 product

DD_Attribute.name: motor_brd_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: Motor Board Temperature

DD_Attribute.name: motor_brd_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: Motor Board Temperature

DD_Attribute.name: motor_pos
DD_Attribute.definition: Filter wheel or focus position

DD_Attribute.name: motor_select
DD_Attribute.definition: Camera number of the active motor

DD_Attribute.name: motor_zone
DD_Attribute.definition: Width of the last home commands index (greater than 31 is 31)

DD_Attribute.name: object
DD_Attribute.definition: Object Name

DD_Attribute.name: ocams_pl_ver
DD_Attribute.definition: Ocams Pipeline Version

DD_Attribute.name: pga1_gain_amp
DD_Attribute.definition: Channel 1 Programmable Gain Amplifier Value

DD_Attribute.name: pga2_gain_amp
DD_Attribute.definition: Channel 2 Programmable Gain Amplifier Value

DD_Attribute.name: phase_angle
DD_Attribute.definition: Phase Angle. The angle between the vector pointing to the Sun and the vector pointing to the Spacecraft. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then sub-spacecraft point shall be used. Allowed range is 0.0 to 180.0

DD_Attribute.name: phase_angle_boresight
DD_Attribute.definition: Intersection-independent Phase Angle. The angle between the vector pointing to the Sun and the vector pointing opposite to the boresight; equal to 180-elongation angle. Allowed range is 0.0 to 180.0

DD_Attribute.name: phase_angle_sis
DD_Attribute.definition: Phase Angle. The angle between the vector pointing to the Sun and the vector pointing to the Spacecraft. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 180.0

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_ccd_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam CCD heater, on/off state

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_ccd_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam CCD resistance temperature detector (RTD) temperature

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_ccd_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam CCD resistance temperature detector (RTD) temperature

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_focus_house_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: State of the heater: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_focus_motor_heater
DD_Attribute.definition: State of the heater: 0 equals off, 1 equals on

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_foh_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam Focus Housing Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_foh_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam Focus Housing Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_fom_temp
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam Focus Motor Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: polycam_fom_temp_x
DD_Attribute.definition: PolyCam Focus Motor Thermistor

DD_Attribute.name: quaternion0
DD_Attribute.definition: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q0 equals cos(t/2)) obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image. SPICE quaternion standard is that Q0 is the scalar value which is followed here.

DD_Attribute.name: quaternion1

Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image.

DD_Attribute.name: quaternion2
DD_Attribute.definition: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q2 equals sin(theta/2))obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image.

DD_Attribute.name: quaternion3
DD_Attribute.definition: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q3 equals sin(theta/2)) obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image.

DD_Attribute.name: solar_azimuth
DD_Attribute.definition: Solar Azimuth. The angle between two half-planes, both bounded by the target rotation axis boresight intersection, one containing Sun, the other parallel to the anti-normal at the boresight intersection. A value of 180.0 represents coincident half-planes; a value of 0.0 represents parallel but opposing half-planes. If Boresight Flag NE 1, the value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 360.0

DD_Attribute.name: solar_mean_normal_az
DD_Attribute.definition: Local-mean-normal-based Solar Time (LST). The angle between two half-planes, both bounded by the target rotation axis boresight intersection, one containing the Sun, the other parallel to the mean anti-normal calculated from up to 100 vectors in the FOV. A value of 180.0 represents coincident half-planes; a value of 0.0 represents parallel but opposing half-planes. If fov_fill_flag is zero, the value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 360.0

DD_Attribute.name: solar_normal_lst
DD_Attribute.definition: Local-normal-based Solar Time (LST). The hour angle between two half-planes, both bounded by the target rotation axis boresight intersection, one containing the Sun, the other parallel to the anti-normal at the boresight intersection. A value of 12.0 represents coincident half-planes; a value of 0.0 represents parallel but opposing half-planes. If Boresight Flag NE 1, the value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 24.0

DD_Attribute.name: spacecraft_azimuth
DD_Attribute.definition: Spacecraft Azimuth. The angle between two half-planes, both bounded by the target rotation axis boresight intersection, one containing the boresight-intersection-tospacecraft vector, the other parallel to the anti-normal at the boresight intersection. A value of 180.0 represents coincident half-planes; a value of 0.0 represents parallel but opposing half-planes. If Boresight Flag NE 1, the value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 360.0

DD_Attribute.name: trans_cmd_compression
DD_Attribute.definition: Compression mode. 0 means no compression; 0xff means lossless compression; 1-99 means JPEG compression quality N, grayscale; 101-199 means JPEG compression quality N, 4:2:2 color subsampling. JPEG compression can only be applied to 8-bit data. Note that if a color camera image is compressed as grayscale, compression efficiency may be degraded. Keyword may be blank if the transmit-image-raw command was used to acquire image.

DD_Attribute.name: trans_cmd_summing
DD_Attribute.definition: Turns 2x2 summing on or off. Legal values are 1 (no summing) and 2 (2x2 summing.) Summing can only be applied to 8-bit data. Images with both compression and summing selected will be compressed but not summed. Keyword may be blank if the transmit-image-raw command was used to acquire image.

DD_Class.name: Common_Instrument_Attributes
DD_Class.definition: Attributes that describe instrument characteristics such as times, temperatures, voltages or pressures that are common to more than one instrument aboard the OSIRIS-REx Spacecraft.

DD_Class.name: Data_Processing_Information
DD_Class.definition: This class contains the data processing information for a specific observation or set of observations. Items included in this class include names of input files used in the data processing, the source (test or flight) of the data, who or where the data was processed, and if necessary software names and version numbers.

DD_Class.name: Data_Quality
DD_Class.definition: This class contains data quality information for a specific observation or set of observations. Attributes can include data quality flags, as well as checksum status.

DD_Class.name: Identification_Info
DD_Class.definition: The Identification_Info Class contains attributes that describe the OSIRIS-REx Science Processing and Operations Center product and working group identification.

DD_Class.name: Instrument_Telemetry_Identification
DD_Class.definition: This class contains the spacecraft telemetry packet type identification information for a specific observation or set of observations.

DD_Class.name: Map_Format
DD_Class.definition: The Map_Format Class contians attributes that describe the array layout of OSIRIS-REx map products.

DD_Class.name: Map_Product
DD_Class.definition: The Map Product class is a class that contains attributes and classes that describe OSIRIS-REx map prodcuts. These prodcuts are described by the OSIRIS-REx Map Formats SIS that can be found in the mission documents collection.

DD_Class.name: Map_Product_Specific
DD_Class.definition: The Map_Product_Specific Class contains attributes that ae specific to the particular map product being labeled.

DD_Class.name: Map_Specific_Information
DD_Class.definition: The Map_Specific_Information Class contains attributes that describe type and scale of the map data product.

DD_Class.name: Mission_Information
DD_Class.definition: This class contains information about the OSIRIS-REx mission and mission phases. The attributes in this class are common to all mission data products.

DD_Class.name: OCAMS_Image_Properties
DD_Class.definition: This class contains the OSIRIS-REx Camera Suite (OCAMS) image properties. Attributes specify the type of image taken for the specific observation.

DD_Class.name: OCAMS_Instrument_Attributes
DD_Class.definition: This class contains instrument attributes specific to the OSIRIS-REx Camera Suite (OCAMS). These instrument attributes are such items as instrument set-up parameters for each image or sequence of images taken, instrument temperatures, voltages and currents, or other parameters recorded by the instrument on an image by image basis.

DD_Class.name: OVIRS_Instrument_Attributes
DD_Class.definition: This class contains instrument attributes specific to OVIRS.

DD_Class.name: Shape_Data_Source
DD_Class.definition: The Shape_Data_Source Class contains attributes that describe the source of the shape data used to in the map data product.

DD_Class.name: Spatial
DD_Class.definition: This class contains spatial information for a specific observation or set of observations that is not otherwise found in the GEOMETRY Discipline Dictionary. Attributes included may be ancillary World Coordinate System (WCS) values or additional quaternion information that should be used with caution.

DD_Class.name: Summary_Spatial_Information
DD_Class.definition: The Summary_Spatial_Information Class contains attributes that describe center and bounding coordinates (center lat/lon, lower left lat/lon, upper right lat/lon, lower right lat/lon, and upper right lat/lon) of the map data product.

DD_Class.name: TAGCAMS_Instrument_Attributes
DD_Class.definition: This class contains instrument attributes specific to the OSIRIS-REx Navigation Camera (TagCam). These instrument attributes are such items as instrument set-up parameters for each image or sequence of images taken, instrument temperatures or other parameters recorded by the instrument on an image by image basis.

DD_Class.name: Tilt_Ellipse
DD_Class.definition: The Tilt_Ellipse Class contains attributes that describe the tilt ellipse of Bennu.

DD_Class.name: Thermal_Specific_Attributes
DD_Class.definition: The Thermal_Specific Class contains attributes that describe attributes specific to the Thermal Analysis Working Group.

DD_Class.name: Time
DD_Class.definition: This class contains timing information for a specific observation or set of observations. This class is a mission type class meaning that the timing values given in this class have been calculated using standard SPICE libraries and the appropriate mission specific SPICE kernels based on the instrument specific spacecraft clock values recorded at the time of the observation.
